Health is the best!!! 
Hello, my name is IMPT.
I have a rare condition called Brugada Syndrome (a type of arrhythmia that causes sudden cardiac death during sleep) and have an implantable cardioverter-defibrillator (ICD) in my left chest.
This inspired me to start YouTube to share positive and healthy information with more people.

I graduated with 4 years of physical education, 2 years of cosmetology, and 4 years of social work.
I studied Taekwondo, Muay Thai, Judo, Aikido, and personal training.
I've taught a lot of people how to exercise.
On my YouTube channel, I will try to explain exercise and health information that is difficult to explain to the general public as concisely and easily as possible. 
I will do my best to deliver good information to you.

Health is the best!!! 
Hello, my name is IMPT.
I have a rare condition called Brugada Syndrome (a type of arrhythmia that causes sudden cardiac death during sleep) and have an implantable cardioverter-defibrillator (ICD) in my left chest.
This inspired me to start YouTube to share positive and healthy information with more people.

I graduated with 4 years of physical education, 2 years of cosmetology, and 4 years of social work.
I studied Taekwondo, Muay Thai, Judo, Aikido, and personal training.
I've taught a lot of people how to exercise.
On my YouTube channel, I will try to explain exercise and health information that is difficult to explain to the general public as concisely and easily as possible. 
I will do my best to deliver good information to you.

IAM IMPT

1. I was obese as a child, so I was interested in dieting earlier than others, but because of the fat cells that were stretched a lot due to the influence of childhood obesity, if I neglected to manage it a little after dieting, I would gain weight again and diet again, and the so-called rubber band body was me. So, while I have been on numerous diets, I have tried various diet methods and no one taught me, and the diet know-how I realized at that time, I will rethink it from my point of view as a beginner and deliver it through YouTube.

2. The beginning of Impity was very simple. I was working as a trainer at a gym in Ichon-dong, East Seoul, and I was teaching a member in his 50s how to stretch when another member asked me, "Can I film you with my phone?" and I improvised and said, "Yes, you can film me, but I'll upload my stretching video to YouTube soon, so it'll be better if you watch it then."   I don't lie, so I started YouTube right away, so I set the difficulty level of the Impeti workout to the standard of people in their 40s to 60s. In fact, people in their 40s and 50s are more fit than people in their 20s and 30s these days, so if you follow it, you will feel that it is a suitable exercise intensity. And because I pursue practicality and efficiency, that is, exercise methods and exercise time that can be followed as soon as possible in order to minimize injuries and easily fit into daily life, I mainly cover short workout videos within 10 minutes, and I also upload workout videos of 15 to 20 minutes in between.

3. I have a rare condition called Brugada syndrome (a type of arrhythmia that causes sudden cardiac death during sleep) and have an implantable cardioverter-defibrillator (ICD) in my left chest. I have a bilateral shoulder imbalance and limited range of motion in my left shoulder, which can make the movement of my left arm look unnatural in certain movements and I could lose more body fat, but then the skin flap below my collarbone that covers the defibrillator would become too thin and uncomfortable, so I have not lost any more weight and am maintaining a moderate weight.

4.I graduated from 4 years of physical education, 2 years of cosmetology, and 4 years of social work.I practice various sports such as taekwondo, muay thai, judo, aikido, and fitness, and have taught many people how to exercise.On my YouTube channel, I will try to explain exercises and health information that are difficult to explain to non-professionals in the most concise and understandable way as possible.Thank you!

I was obese as a child, so I was interested in dieting earlier than others, but because of the fat cells that were stretched a lot due to the influence of childhood obesity, if I neglected to manage it a little after dieting, I would gain weight again and diet again, and the so-called rubber band body was me. So, while I have been on numerous diets, I have tried various diet methods and no one taught me, and the diet know-how I realized at that time, I will rethink it from my point of view as a beginner and deliver it through YouTube.

2. The beginning of Impity was very simple. I was working as a trainer at a gym in Ichon-dong, East Seoul, and I was teaching a member in his 50s how to stretch when another member asked me, "Can I film you with my phone?" and I improvised and said, "Yes, you can film me, but I'll upload my stretching video to YouTube soon, so it'll be better if you watch it then."   I don't lie, so I started YouTube right away, so I set the difficulty level of the Impeti workout to the standard of people in their 40s to 60s. In fact, people in their 40s and 50s are more fit than people in their 20s and 30s these days, so if you follow it, you will feel that it is a suitable exercise intensity. And because I pursue practicality and efficiency, that is, exercise methods and exercise time that can be followed as soon as possible in order to minimize injuries and easily fit into daily life, I mainly cover short workout videos within 10 minutes, and I also upload workout videos of 15 to 20 minutes in between.

3. I have a rare condition called Brugada syndrome (a type of arrhythmia that causes sudden cardiac death during sleep) and have an implantable cardioverter-defibrillator (ICD) in my left chest. I have a bilateral shoulder imbalance and limited range of motion in my left shoulder, which can make the movement of my left arm look unnatural in certain movements and I could lose more body fat, but then the skin flap below my collarbone that covers the defibrillator would become too thin and uncomfortable, so I have not lost any more weight and am maintaining a moderate weight.

4.I graduated from 4 years of physical education, 2 years of cosmetology, and 4 years of social work.I practice various sports such as taekwondo, muay thai, judo, aikido, and fitness, and have taught many people how to exercise.On my YouTube channel, I will try to explain exercises and health information that are difficult to explain to non-professionals in the most concise and understandable way as possible.Thank you!

IAM IMPT

1. I was obese as a child, so I was interested in dieting earlier than others, but because of the fat cells that were stretched a lot due to the influence of childhood obesity, if I neglected to manage it a little after dieting, I would gain weight again and diet again, and the so-called rubber band body was me. So, while I have been on numerous diets, I have tried various diet methods and no one taught me, and the diet know-how I realized at that time, I will rethink it from my point of view as a beginner and deliver it through YouTube.

2. The beginning of Impity was very simple. I was working as a trainer at a gym in Ichon-dong, East Seoul, and I was teaching a member in his 50s how to stretch when another member asked me, "Can I film you with my phone?" and I improvised and said, "Yes, you can film me, but I'll upload my stretching video to YouTube soon, so it'll be better if you watch it then."   I don't lie, so I started YouTube right away, so I set the difficulty level of the Impeti workout to the standard of people in their 40s to 60s. In fact, people in their 40s and 50s are more fit than people in their 20s and 30s these days, so if you follow it, you will feel that it is a suitable exercise intensity. And because I pursue practicality and efficiency, that is, exercise methods and exercise time that can be followed as soon as possible in order to minimize injuries and easily fit into daily life, I mainly cover short workout videos within 10 minutes, and I also upload workout videos of 15 to 20 minutes in between.

3. I have a rare condition called Brugada syndrome (a type of arrhythmia that causes sudden cardiac death during sleep) and have an implantable cardioverter-defibrillator (ICD) in my left chest. I have a bilateral shoulder imbalance and limited range of motion in my left shoulder, which can make the movement of my left arm look unnatural in certain movements and I could lose more body fat, but then the skin flap below my collarbone that covers the defibrillator would become too thin and uncomfortable, so I have not lost any more weight and am maintaining a moderate weight.

4.I graduated from 4 years of physical education, 2 years of cosmetology, and 4 years of social work.I practice various sports such as taekwondo, muay thai, judo, aikido, and fitness, and have taught many people how to exercise.On my YouTube channel, I will try to explain exercises and health information that are difficult to explain to non-professionals in the most concise and understandable way as possible.Thank you!

Hello, my name is IMPT.
I have a rare condition called Brugada Syndrome (a type of arrhythmia that causes sudden cardiac death during sleep) and have an implantable cardioverter-defibrillator (ICD) in my left chest.
This inspired me to start YouTube to share positive and healthy information with more people.

I graduated with 4 years of physical education, 2 years of cosmetology, and 4 years of social work.
I studied Taekwondo, Muay Thai, Judo, Aikido, and personal training.
I've taught a lot of people how to exercise.
On my YouTube channel, I will try to explain exercise and health information that is difficult to explain to the general public as concisely and easily as possible. 
I will do my best to deliver good information to you.

Health is the best!!! 
Hello, my name is IMPT.
I have a rare condition called Brugada Syndrome (a type of arrhythmia that causes sudden cardiac death during sleep) and have an implantable cardioverter-defibrillator (ICD) in my left chest.
This inspired me to start YouTube to share positive and healthy information with more people.

I graduated with 4 years of physical education, 2 years of cosmetology, and 4 years of social work.
I studied Taekwondo, Muay Thai, Judo, Aikido, and personal training.
I've taught a lot of people how to exercise.
On my YouTube channel, I will try to explain exercise and health information that is difficult to explain to the general public as concisely and easily as possible. 
I will do my best to deliver good information to you.

IAM IMPT

1. I was obese as a child, so I was interested in dieting earlier than others, but because of the fat cells that were stretched a lot due to the influence of childhood obesity, if I neglected to manage it a little after dieting, I would gain weight again and diet again, and the so-called rubber band body was me. So, while I have been on numerous diets, I have tried various diet methods and no one taught me, and the diet know-how I realized at that time, I will rethink it from my point of view as a beginner and deliver it through YouTube.

2. The beginning of Impity was very simple. I was working as a trainer at a gym in Ichon-dong, East Seoul, and I was teaching a member in his 50s how to stretch when another member asked me, "Can I film you with my phone?" and I improvised and said, "Yes, you can film me, but I'll upload my stretching video to YouTube soon, so it'll be better if you watch it then."   I don't lie, so I started YouTube right away, so I set the difficulty level of the Impeti workout to the standard of people in their 40s to 60s. In fact, people in their 40s and 50s are more fit than people in their 20s and 30s these days, so if you follow it, you will feel that it is a suitable exercise intensity. And because I pursue practicality and efficiency, that is, exercise methods and exercise time that can be followed as soon as possible in order to minimize injuries and easily fit into daily life, I mainly cover short workout videos within 10 minutes, and I also upload workout videos of 15 to 20 minutes in between.

3. I have a rare condition called Brugada syndrome (a type of arrhythmia that causes sudden cardiac death during sleep) and have an implantable cardioverter-defibrillator (ICD) in my left chest. I have a bilateral shoulder imbalance and limited range of motion in my left shoulder, which can make the movement of my left arm look unnatural in certain movements and I could lose more body fat, but then the skin flap below my collarbone that covers the defibrillator would become too thin and uncomfortable, so I have not lost any more weight and am maintaining a moderate weight.

4.I graduated from 4 years of physical education, 2 years of cosmetology, and 4 years of social work.I practice various sports such as taekwondo, muay thai, judo, aikido, and fitness, and have taught many people how to exercise.On my YouTube channel, I will try to explain exercises and health information that are difficult to explain to non-professionals in the most concise and understandable way as possible.Thank you!

IAM IMPT

1. I was obese as a child, so I was interested in dieting earlier than others, but because of the fat cells that were stretched a lot due to the influence of childhood obesity, if I neglected to manage it a little after dieting, I would gain weight again and diet again, and the so-called rubber band body was me. So, while I have been on numerous diets, I have tried various diet methods and no one taught me, and the diet know-how I realized at that time, I will rethink it from my point of view as a beginner and deliver it through YouTube.

2. The beginning of Impity was very simple. I was working as a trainer at a gym in Ichon-dong, East Seoul, and I was teaching a member in his 50s how to stretch when another member asked me, "Can I film you with my phone?" and I improvised and said, "Yes, you can film me, but I'll upload my stretching video to YouTube soon, so it'll be better if you watch it then."   I don't lie, so I started YouTube right away, so I set the difficulty level of the Impeti workout to the standard of people in their 40s to 60s. In fact, people in their 40s and 50s are more fit than people in their 20s and 30s these days, so if you follow it, you will feel that it is a suitable exercise intensity. And because I pursue practicality and efficiency, that is, exercise methods and exercise time that can be followed as soon as possible in order to minimize injuries and easily fit into daily life, I mainly cover short workout videos within 10 minutes, and I also upload workout videos of 15 to 20 minutes in between.

3. I have a rare condition called Brugada syndrome (a type of arrhythmia that causes sudden cardiac death during sleep) and have an implantable cardioverter-defibrillator (ICD) in my left chest. I have a bilateral shoulder imbalance and limited range of motion in my left shoulder, which can make the movement of my left arm look unnatural in certain movements and I could lose more body fat, but then the skin flap below my collarbone that covers the defibrillator would become too thin and uncomfortable, so I have not lost any more weight and am maintaining a moderate weight.

4.I graduated from 4 years of physical education, 2 years of cosmetology, and 4 years of social work.I practice various sports such as taekwondo, muay thai, judo, aikido, and fitness, and have taught many people how to exercise.On my YouTube channel, I will try to explain exercises and health information that are difficult to explain to non-professionals in the most concise and understandable way as possible.Thank you!

IAM IMPT

1. I was obese as a child, so I was interested in dieting earlier than others, but because of the fat cells that were stretched a lot due to the influence of childhood obesity, if I neglected to manage it a little after dieting, I would gain weight again and diet again, and the so-called rubber band body was me. So, while I have been on numerous diets, I have tried various diet methods and no one taught me, and the diet know-how I realized at that time, I will rethink it from my point of view as a beginner and deliver it through YouTube.

2. The beginning of Impity was very simple. I was working as a trainer at a gym in Ichon-dong, East Seoul, and I was teaching a member in his 50s how to stretch when another member asked me, "Can I film you with my phone?" and I improvised and said, "Yes, you can film me, but I'll upload my stretching video to YouTube soon, so it'll be better if you watch it then."   I don't lie, so I started YouTube right away, so I set the difficulty level of the Impeti workout to the standard of people in their 40s to 60s. In fact, people in their 40s and 50s are more fit than people in their 20s and 30s these days, so if you follow it, you will feel that it is a suitable exercise intensity. And because I pursue practicality and efficiency, that is, exercise methods and exercise time that can be followed as soon as possible in order to minimize injuries and easily fit into daily life, I mainly cover short workout videos within 10 minutes, and I also upload workout videos of 15 to 20 minutes in between.

3. I have a rare condition called Brugada syndrome (a type of arrhythmia that causes sudden cardiac death during sleep) and have an implantable cardioverter-defibrillator (ICD) in my left chest. I have a bilateral shoulder imbalance and limited range of motion in my left shoulder, which can make the movement of my left arm look unnatural in certain movements and I could lose more body fat, but then the skin flap below my collarbone that covers the defibrillator would become too thin and uncomfortable, so I have not lost any more weight and am maintaining a moderate weight.

4.I graduated from 4 years of physical education, 2 years of cosmetology, and 4 years of social work.I practice various sports such as taekwondo, muay thai, judo, aikido, and fitness, and have taught many people how to exercise.On my YouTube channel, I will try to explain exercises and health information that are difficult to explain to non-professionals in the most concise and understandable way as possible.Thank you!

IAM IMPT

1. I was obese as a child, so I was interested in dieting earlier than others, but because of the fat cells that were stretched a lot due to the influence of childhood obesity, if I neglected to manage it a little after dieting, I would gain weight again and diet again, and the so-called rubber band body was me. So, while I have been on numerous diets, I have tried various diet methods and no one taught me, and the diet know-how I realized at that time, I will rethink it from my point of view as a beginner and deliver it through YouTube.

2. The beginning of Impity was very simple. I was working as a trainer at a gym in Ichon-dong, East Seoul, and I was teaching a member in his 50s how to stretch when another member asked me, "Can I film you with my phone?" and I improvised and said, "Yes, you can film me, but I'll upload my stretching video to YouTube soon, so it'll be better if you watch it then."   I don't lie, so I started YouTube right away, so I set the difficulty level of the Impeti workout to the standard of people in their 40s to 60s. In fact, people in their 40s and 50s are more fit than people in their 20s and 30s these days, so if you follow it, you will feel that it is a suitable exercise intensity. And because I pursue practicality and efficiency, that is, exercise methods and exercise time that can be followed as soon as possible in order to minimize injuries and easily fit into daily life, I mainly cover short workout videos within 10 minutes, and I also upload workout videos of 15 to 20 minutes in between.

3. I have a rare condition called Brugada syndrome (a type of arrhythmia that causes sudden cardiac death during sleep) and have an implantable cardioverter-defibrillator (ICD) in my left chest. I have a bilateral shoulder imbalance and limited range of motion in my left shoulder, which can make the movement of my left arm look unnatural in certain movements and I could lose more body fat, but then the skin flap below my collarbone that covers the defibrillator would become too thin and uncomfortable, so I have not lost any more weight and am maintaining a moderate weight.

4.I graduated from 4 years of physical education, 2 years of cosmetology, and 4 years of social work.I practice various sports such as taekwondo, muay thai, judo, aikido, and fitness, and have taught many people how to exercise.On my YouTube channel, I will try to explain exercises and health information that are difficult to explain to non-professionals in the most concise and understandable way as possible.Thank you!

Health is the best!!! 
Hello, my name is IMPT.
I have a rare condition called Brugada Syndrome (a type of arrhythmia that causes sudden cardiac death during sleep) and have an implantable cardioverter-defibrillator (ICD) in my left chest.
This inspired me to start YouTube to share positive and healthy information with more people.

I graduated with 4 years of physical education, 2 years of cosmetology, and 4 years of social work.
I studied Taekwondo, Muay Thai, Judo, Aikido, and personal training.
I've taught a lot of people how to exercise.
On my YouTube channel, I will try to explain exercise and health information that is difficult to explain to the general public as concisely and easily as possible. 
I will do my best to deliver good information to you.

Health is the best!!! 
Hello, my name is IMPT.
I have a rare condition called Brugada Syndrome (a type of arrhythmia that causes sudden cardiac death during sleep) and have an implantable cardioverter-defibrillator (ICD) in my left chest.
This inspired me to start YouTube to share positive and healthy information with more people.

I graduated with 4 years of physical education, 2 years of cosmetology, and 4 years of social work.
I studied Taekwondo, Muay Thai, Judo, Aikido, and personal training.
I've taught a lot of people how to exercise.
On my YouTube channel, I will try to explain exercise and health information that is difficult to explain to the general public as concisely and easily as possible. 
I will do my best to deliver good information to you.

Health is the best!!! 
Hello, my name is IMPT.
I have a rare condition called Brugada Syndrome (a type of arrhythmia that causes sudden cardiac death during sleep) and have an implantable cardioverter-defibrillator (ICD) in my left chest.
This inspired me to start YouTube to share positive and healthy information with more people.

I graduated with 4 years of physical education, 2 years of cosmetology, and 4 years of social work.
I studied Taekwondo, Muay Thai, Judo, Aikido, and personal training.
I've taught a lot of people how to exercise.
On my YouTube channel, I will try to explain exercise and health information that is difficult to explain to the general public as concisely and easily as possible. 
I will do my best to deliver good information to you.

Hello, my name is IMPT.

I will do my best to deliver good information to you.

IAM IMPT

1. I was obese as a child, so I was interested in dieting earlier than others, but because of the fat cells that were stretched a lot due to the influence of childhood obesity, if I neglected to manage it a little after dieting, I would gain weight again and diet again, and the so-called rubber band body was me. So, while I have been on numerous diets, I have tried various diet methods and no one taught me, and the diet know-how I realized at that time, I will rethink it from my point of view as a beginner and deliver it through YouTube.

2. The beginning of Impity was very simple. I was working as a trainer at a gym in Ichon-dong, East Seoul, and I was teaching a member in his 50s how to stretch when another member asked me, "Can I film you with my phone?" and I improvised and said, "Yes, you can film me, but I'll upload my stretching video to YouTube soon, so it'll be better if you watch it then."   I don't lie, so I started YouTube right away, so I set the difficulty level of the Impeti workout to the standard of people in their 40s to 60s. In fact, people in their 40s and 50s are more fit than people in their 20s and 30s these days, so if you follow it, you will feel that it is a suitable exercise intensity. And because I pursue practicality and efficiency, that is, exercise methods and exercise time that can be followed as soon as possible in order to minimize injuries and easily fit into daily life, I mainly cover short workout videos within 10 minutes, and I also upload workout videos of 15 to 20 minutes in between.

3. I have a rare condition called Brugada syndrome (a type of arrhythmia that causes sudden cardiac death during sleep) and have an implantable cardioverter-defibrillator (ICD) in my left chest. I have a bilateral shoulder imbalance and limited range of motion in my left shoulder, which can make the movement of my left arm look unnatural in certain movements and I could lose more body fat, but then the skin flap below my collarbone that covers the defibrillator would become too thin and uncomfortable, so I have not lost any more weight and am maintaining a moderate weight.

4.I graduated from 4 years of physical education, 2 years of cosmetology, and 4 years of social work.I practice various sports such as taekwondo, muay thai, judo, aikido, and fitness, and have taught many people how to exercise.On my YouTube channel, I will try to explain exercises and health information that are difficult to explain to non-professionals in the most concise and understandable way as possible.Thank you!

IAM IMPT

1. I was obese as a child, so I was interested in dieting earlier than others, but because of the fat cells that were stretched a lot due to the influence of childhood obesity, if I neglected to manage it a little after dieting, I would gain weight again and diet again, and the so-called rubber band body was me. So, while I have been on numerous diets, I have tried various diet methods and no one taught me, and the diet know-how I realized at that time, I will rethink it from my point of view as a beginner and deliver it through YouTube.

2. The beginning of Impity was very simple. I was working as a trainer at a gym in Ichon-dong, East Seoul, and I was teaching a member in his 50s how to stretch when another member asked me, "Can I film you with my phone?" and I improvised and said, "Yes, you can film me, but I'll upload my stretching video to YouTube soon, so it'll be better if you watch it then."   I don't lie, so I started YouTube right away, so I set the difficulty level of the Impeti workout to the standard of people in their 40s to 60s. In fact, people in their 40s and 50s are more fit than people in their 20s and 30s these days, so if you follow it, you will feel that it is a suitable exercise intensity. And because I pursue practicality and efficiency, that is, exercise methods and exercise time that can be followed as soon as possible in order to minimize injuries and easily fit into daily life, I mainly cover short workout videos within 10 minutes, and I also upload workout videos of 15 to 20 minutes in between.

3. I have a rare condition called Brugada syndrome (a type of arrhythmia that causes sudden cardiac death during sleep) and have an implantable cardioverter-defibrillator (ICD) in my left chest. I have a bilateral shoulder imbalance and limited range of motion in my left shoulder, which can make the movement of my left arm look unnatural in certain movements and I could lose more body fat, but then the skin flap below my collarbone that covers the defibrillator would become too thin and uncomfortable, so I have not lost any more weight and am maintaining a moderate weight.

4.I graduated from 4 years of physical education, 2 years of cosmetology, and 4 years of social work.I practice various sports such as taekwondo, muay thai, judo, aikido, and fitness, and have taught many people how to exercise.On my YouTube channel, I will try to explain exercises and health information that are difficult to explain to non-professionals in the most concise and understandable way as possible.Thank you!

IAM IMPT

1. I was obese as a child, so I was interested in dieting earlier than others, but because of the fat cells that were stretched a lot due to the influence of childhood obesity, if I neglected to manage it a little after dieting, I would gain weight again and diet again, and the so-called rubber band body was me. 2. The beginning of Impity was very simple. I was working as a trainer at a gym in Ichon-dong, East Seoul, and I was teaching a member in his 50s how to stretch when another member asked me, "Can I film you with my phone?" and I improvised and said, "Yes, you can film me, but I'll upload my stretching video to YouTube soon, so it'll be better if you watch it then." 3. I have a rare condition called Brugada syndrome (a type of arrhythmia that causes sudden cardiac death during sleep) and have an implantable cardioverter-defibrillator (ICD) in my left chest. I have a bilateral shoulder imbalance and limited range of motion in my left shoulder, which can make the movement of my left arm look unnatural in certain movements and I could lose more body fat, but then the skin flap below my collarbone that covers the defibrillator would become too thin and uncomfortable, so I have not lost any more weight and am maintaining a moderate weight.

4.I graduated from 4 years of physical education, 2 years of cosmetology, and 4 years of social work.I practice various sports such as taekwondo, muay thai, judo, aikido, and fitness, and have taught many people how to exercise.On my YouTube channel, I will try to explain exercises and health information that are difficult to explain to non-professionals in the most concise and understandable way as possible.Thank you!

Health is the best!!! 
Hello, my name is IMPT.
I have a rare condition called Brugada Syndrome (a type of arrhythmia that causes sudden cardiac death during sleep) and have an implantable cardioverter-defibrillator (ICD) in my left chest.
This inspired me to start YouTube to share positive and healthy information with more people.

I graduated with 4 years of physical education, 2 years of cosmetology, and 4 years of social work.
I studied Taekwondo, Muay Thai, Judo, Aikido, and personal training.
I've taught a lot of people how to exercise.
On my YouTube channel, I will try to explain exercise and health information that is difficult to explain to the general public as concisely and easily as possible. 
I will do my best to deliver good information to you.
